RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snack
<hw>Snack</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Snatch</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A share; a part or portion; --
obsolete, except in the colloquial phrase, <cref>to go snacks</cref>, i.
e., to share.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At last he whispers, ⟦ldquo⟧Do, and we <qex>go
snacks</qex>.⟦rdquo⟧</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slight, hasty repast.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snacket</ent>⟦br⟧
